Description:
AN ESTIMATED 215 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE. SOME OF THEIR ACTIVITIES WILL INCLUDE 

-VISITING AND ASSISTING HOMEBOUND SENIORS/THOSE WITH DISABILITIES WITH DAILY LIVING ACTIVITIES IN THEIR HOMES, SO THAT THEY CAN LIVE INDEPENDENTLY AS LONG AS THEY ARE ABLE; 
-DELIVERING NUTRITIOUS MEALS/GROCERIES TO HOMEBOUND SENIORS AND THOSE WITH DISABILITIES SO THAT THEY CAN MAINTAIN AND/OR IMPROVE THEIR HEALTH WHILE ALSO LIVING INDEPENDENTLY;
-PROVIDING HEALTH EDUCATION CLASSES, PROGRAMS, AND ACTIVITIES TO SENIORS, INCLUDING PHYSICAL EXERCISE, NUTRITION, AND MENTAL HEALTH, SO THAT THEY CAN LIVE LONGER AND STRONGER LIVES; 
-RAISING MONEY THROUGH THRIFT SHOP SALES SO THAT PRESCHOOL SCHOLARSHIPS CAN BE OFFERED TO CHILDREN OF LOW-INCOME FAMILIES; 
-SUPPORTING DISADVANTAGED CHILDREN IN PRESCHOOLS AND GRADE SCHOOLS THROUGH TUTORING, CLASSROOM SUPPORT, AND EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES DESIGNED SO THAT CHILDREN WILL REMAIN IN AND SUCCEED IN SCHOOL SETTINGS; 
-SUPPORTING COMMUNITY AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROJECTS THROUGH HABITAT; AND
- INCREASING FOOD SECURITY BY ASSISTING IN THE FOOD BANK'S WAREHOUSE.

THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF THIS PROJECT IS HEALTHY FUTURES. AT THE END OF THE THREE-YEAR GRANT, 95 HOMEBOUND SENIORS, VETERANS, AND INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES WILL HAVE DEVELOPED RELATIONSHIPS WITH VOLUNTEERS THAT IMPROVE THEIR CAPACITY FOR INDEPENDENT LIVING AND 60 WILL HAVE INCREASED HEALTH KNOWLEDGE AS A RESULT OF RSVP-SUPPORTED HEALTH EDUCATION PROGRAMS.  THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $100,713 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $43,174.

AN ESTIMATED 300+ RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE THE CITY OF MESQUITE, NV AND OUTLYING AREAS IN MULTIPLE VOLUNTEER STATIONS. OF THIS NUMBER, AT LEAST 85 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL BE PLACED IN SPECIFIC FOCUS OUTCOME ASSIGNMENTS. SOME OF THEIR ACTIVITIES WILL INCLUDE: 
-AGING IN PLACE: ESTABLISHING A SENIOR DAY CENTER TO PROVIDE SENIORS OPPORTUNITY FOR SOCIALIZATION AND CAREGIVERS' OPPORTUNITY FOR RESPITE AND SENIORS SOCIALIZATION OPPORTUNITIES;
-ACCESS TO HEALTHCARE: PROVIDE SENIORS EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES-MEDICARE FRAUD PREVENTION, ELDER ABUSE PREVENTION, AND DEMENTIA/ALZHEIMER'S EDUCATION, ALL TO IMPROVE ACCESS TO PRIMARY AND PREVENTATIVE HEALTHCARE;
-FOOD PANTRY SUPPORT: ASSIST IN SORTING AND DISTRIBUTING FOOD SPECIFIC TO SENIOR POPULATION, AND 
-VETERANS & MILITARY FAMILIES: SUPPORT LOCAL VETERAN OUTREACH CENTER TO ENCOURAGE ADDITIONAL PARTNERSHIPS WITHIN THE COMMUNITY, I.E. SCHOOL/STUDENT EDUCATIONAL TOURS, ETC.  
-EDUCATION: TUTORING CHILDREN AT THE SAFEKEY AFTERSCHOOL PROGRAM LOCATED AT VIRGIN VALLEY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL AND POTENTIAL NEW SAFEKEY SITE AT BUNKERVILLE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL; 
THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF THIS PROJECT IS HEALTHY FUTURES. AT THE END OF THE THREE-YEAR GRANT,  ANTICIPATED OUTCOME WILL INCLUDE SENIORS PARTICIPATING IN DAY CENTER ACTIVITIES TO RECEIVE SOCIALIZATION AND HEALTHCARE EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES IN A SUPERVISED SETTING; A NUTRITIONALLY BALANCED MEAL, WHILE ALLOWING CAREGIVERS THE OPPORTUNITY FOR A BREAK, THUS ENCOURAGING CONTINUED AT HOME CARE.  
IN THE AREA OF EDUCATION, RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL PROVIDE TUTORING AND MENTORING TO K-6 STUDENTS. 
THE CORPORATION FOR NATIONAL AND COMMUNITY SERVICE (CNCS) FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF  $85,247 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY A MINIMUM 30% THROUGH IN-KIND/REQUIRED MATCH, GRANT WRITING AND POTENTIAL FUNDRAISING EFFORTS.

RSVP OF NORTHWEST VERMONT HAS BEEN MOBILIZING VOLUNTEERS IN OUR COMMUNITY FOR MORE THAN 40 YEARS.  A SPONSORED PROGRAM OF UNITED WAY OF NORTHWEST VERMONT (UWNWVT), RSVP IS PART OF UWNWVT'S COMMUNITY IMPACT & VOLUNTEER MOBILIZATION DEPARTMENT WHICH ALSO INCLUDES THE UWNWVT VOLUNTEER CENTER.  UWNWVT STRIVES TO UNITE OUR COMMUNITY IN ORDER TO SOLVE COMPLEX COMMUNITY PROBLEMS AND CREATE A STRONGER NORTHWEST VERMONT. 

UWNWVT ACCOMPLISHES THIS MISSION THROUGH STRATEGIC INVESTMENT OF FINANCIAL RESOURCES AS WELL AS VOLUNTEER INVESTMENTS THROUGH UWNWVT SENIOR CORPS PROGRAMS SUCH AS RSVP AND FGP, AND THEIR BROADER MOBILIZATION OF VOLUNTEERS THROUGH COMMUNITY-WIDE RECRUITMENT AND REFERRAL EFFORTS. THIS VOLUNTEER MOBILIZATION EFFORT AIMS TO ACHIEVE UWNWVT'S GOALS OF ENSURING THAT CHILDREN, YOUTH AND YOUNG ADULTS ACHIEVE THEIR POTENTIAL; ALL PEOPLE ARE FINANCIALLY STABLE; AND ALL PEOPLE HAVE OPTIMAL HEALTH AND WELL-BEING. 

AN ESTIMATED 200 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL CONTRIBUTE THEIR TIME AND TALENT TO THESE EFFORTS. OF THIS NUMBER, 90 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL BE PLACED IN OUTCOME ASSIGNMENTS.     

THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF OUR PROJECT IS EDUCATION.  AT THE END OF THE THREE YEAR GRANT PERIOD AT LEAST 45 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL BE WORKING WITH YOUNG CHILDREN WITHIN OUR SIGNATURE PROGRAMS "READ TO ME" AND "SCHOOL BUDDIES" PROMOTING PRE-LITERACY SKILLS IN EARLY CHILDCARE SETTINGS AND TUTORING IN ELEMENTARY AND MIDDLE SCHOOL CLASSROOMS.  ANOTHER 45 VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE IN THE AREA OF HEALTHY FUTURES: 15 PROVIDING TRANSPORTATION FOR OLDER ADULTS AND PERSONS WITH DISABILITIES TO MEDICAL AND LIFE ENRICHING APPOINTMENTS AND 30 LEADING BONE BUILDERS CLASSES TO BUILD HEALTHY PRACTICES AND REDUCE THE IMPACT OF OSTEOPOROSIS. EACH WORK PLAN WITHIN THESE FOCUS AREAS WAS DEVELOPED BASED ON A STRONG UNDERSTANDING OF OUR COMMUNITY NEEDS, ASSETS AND OPPORTUNITIES.

ANTICIPATED OUTCOMES OF THE VOLUNTEER WORK OUTLINED IN OUR WORK PLANS INCLUDE:
*YOUNG CHILDREN WILL DEVELOP PRE-LITERACY SKILLS THAT PREPARE THEM FOR SUCCESS IN SCHOOL;
*ELEMENTARY AND MIDDLE SCHOOL CHILDREN WILL IMPROVE THEIR COMPETENCY IN LITERACY, MATH AND OTHER ACADEMIC AREAS THAT WILL HELP THEM GAIN CONFIDENCE, STAY ENGAGED AND SUCCEED IN SCHOOL;
*SENIORS AND PEOPLE WITH DISABILITIES WILL EXPERIENCE GREATER SOCIAL CONNECTION, LESS ISOLATION, IMPROVED NUTRITION AND HEALTH BECAUSE OF ACCESS TO TRANSPORTATION SERVICES FOR MEDICAL APPOINTMENTS AS WELL AS LIFE ENRICHING ACTIVITIES; 
*SENIORS WILL BE STRONGER, SAFER, BETTER CONNECTED, AND MORE PHYSICALLY ACTIVE THROUGH PARTICIPATION IN THE RSVP BONE BUILDERS PROGRAM.  

THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $89,513 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $70,878 IN NON-FEDERAL RESOURCES.

AN ESTIMATED 750 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE.  OF THIS NUMBER, 52 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL BE PLACED IN OUTCOME ASSIGNMENTS.  SOME OF THEIR ACTIVITIES WILL INCLUDE:
* DELIVERING HOT, NUTRITIOUS MEALS TO HOMEBOUND ELDERLY AND DISABLED INDIVIDUALS;
* SERVING IN COMMUNITY MINISTRY SITES TO ASSIST THE LOW-INCOME POPULATION TO MEET THEIR FOOD AND HOUSEHOLD NEEDS;
* SERVING AT THE VETERANS ADMINISTRATION FACILITY;
* WORKING WITH OUR LOCAL HABITAT FOR HUMANITY AFFILIATES TO CONSTRUCT OR RENOVATE HOMES, WITH THE GOAL OF SEEING LOW-INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS MOVED INTO DECENT, AFFORDABLE HOUSING;
* VOLUNTEERING AT OTHER NON-PROFIT COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS.

THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF THIS PROJECT IS HEALTHY FUTURES.  AT THE END OF THE THREE-YEAR GRANT, 958 HOMEBOUND OLDER ADULTS OR HANDICAPPED INDIVIDUALS WILL HAVE RECEIVED MEALS TO ALLOW THEM TO REMAIN IN THEIR HOMES AND 5,000 INDIVIDUALS WILL BE SERVED THROUGH LOCAL AGENCIES ADDRESSING THE NEEDS OF LOW-INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS.  THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $52,312 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $12,500 LOCAL SUPPORT (PROJECTED TO BE RECEIVED ANNUALLY) AND $11,960 IN-KIND OFFICE SPACE (PROJECTED TO BE RECEIVED ANNUALLY).

THE SENIOR CITIZENS ASSOCIATION (SCA) IN FLORENCE COUNTY IS A PRIVATE, NON-PROFIT, COMMUNITY-BASED ORGANIZATION. SCA'S MISSION IS TO PROVIDE A FULL RANGE OF SERVICES TO FLORENCE COUNTY'S SENIOR CITIZENS. THE PURPOSE OF THESE SERVICES IS TO PROMOTE THE PHYSICAL, MENTAL AND SOCIAL WELL-BEING OF SENIOR CITIZENS, ENHANCING THEIR QUALITY OF LIFE AND PROVIDING ASSISTANCE IN MAINTAINING INDEPENDENCE AND PERSONAL GROWTH. 
THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF FLORENCE RSVP IS HEALTHY FUTURES.  CURRENTLY, AN ESTIMATED 261 VOLUNTEERS ARE MEMBERS OF FLORENCE RSVP. OF THIS NUMBER, 223 ARE CURRENTLY IN ONE OR MORE PLACEMENTS AND 123 UNDUPLICATED VOLUNTEERS SERVE IN OUTCOME ASSIGNMENTS INCLUDING HOME DELIVERED MEAL PACKAGING AND DELIVERY, MEDICAL TRANSPORTATION FOR VETERANS, INCOME TAX PREPARATION FOR LOW INCOME INDIVIDUALS, ASSISTING IN HEAD START CLASSROOMS, AND WORK IN SOUP KITCHENS AND FOOD BANKS.  AN ADDITIONAL 100 UNDUPLICATED VOLUNTEERS SERVE IN OTHER COMMUNITY PRIORITIES.  AT THE END OF THE THREE YEAR GRANT, FLORENCE RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SUPPORT THE FOLLOWING OUTCOMES:
-  INCREASED SOCIAL TIES/PERCEIVED SOCIAL SUPPORT FOR OLDER ADULTS;
-  ADDITIONAL VETERANS HAVING ACCESS TO PRIMARY AND PREVENTIVE HEALTH CARE;
-  SUCCESSFUL GAINS IN LITERACY SKILLS AMONG CHILDREN TUTORED BY RSVP VOLUNTEERS;
- MORE ECONOMICALLY DISADVANTAGED INDIVIDUALS RECEIVING FINANCIAL LITERACY SERVICES.
THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $40,000 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $18,284 FROM SENIOR CITIZENS ASSOCIATION.

